The Council of Innkeepers is a Sigilian organization based in the [Guildhall Ward] that sets standard rates of employment for service industry workers (waiters, cooks, etc.) as well as using its buying power to set prices for standard goods necessary in all inns.
Members of the Council of Innkeepers wear a crimson sash edged with gold lace.
The current head of the Council of Innkeepers is Bryn Ohme.
Source: In the Cage: A Guide to Sigil
